      },
      "edited" : false,
      "score" : 1,
      "creation_date" : 1558384170,
      "post_id" : 2417552,
      "comment_id" : 99075828,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "Yes, for portability, do <b>not</b> use backslash. Use forward slash <code>&#47;</code> or the system separator <code>File.separator</code>. Both of those seem to work everywhere. While <code>File.separator</code> is guaranteed to work everywhere, the simple slash <code>&#47;</code> also seems to work everywhere. If it doesn&#39;t work somewhere, then I&#39;d love to hear about it. I believe it will work on all systems. At the very least, I have yet to find anywhere that <code>&#47;</code> doesn&#39;t work (Mac OSX, Windows, *nix, Android, iOS -- I haven&#39;t checked pre OSX Macs that used &quot;:&quot; as a separator though, OS/2, NeXT, or any of the other really ancient OS&#39;s)."
    } ],
