      "comment_id" : 68266345,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "That&#39;s a different scenario to the question.  ClassLoader&#39;s getResourceAsStream method does not take a File path, but a <i>resource name</i> which may or may not be on the file system and is <a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/api/java/lang/Class.html#getResourceAsStream(java.lang.String)\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">documented</a> as only accepting &#39;/&#39; as the resource path separator."
