      "comment_id" : 99075597,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "@Stephan there is no funny escaping there, since <code>File.separator</code> is a backslash. It&#39;s only in hard-coded strings where it is treated as an escape character where you need to escape the backslash. If you&#39;ve stored the character in a text file, or in a <code>char</code> or <code>String</code> then you don&#39;t need to escape it a 2nd time as it&#39;s already been converted to the expected backslash character. Try this to see for yourself: <code>String backslash = &quot;\\\\&quot;; System.out.println(&quot;welcome&quot; + backslash + &quot;to&quot; + backslash + &quot;reality&quot;);</code>"
